362 U.S. 389

80 S.Ct. 811

4 L.Ed.2d 864

Ernest Dossy YANCY
v.
UNITED STATES.

No. 47.

Supreme Court of the United States

April 18, 1960

Mr. Seymour B. Goldman, for petitioner.

Mr. John L. Murphy (Solicitor General Rankin, Assistant Attorney General Wilkey, Messrs. Robert S. Erdahl and J. F. Bishop, on the brief), for the United States.

On writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit.

PER CURIAM.

1

The judgment is affirmed by an equally divided Court.

2

Mr. Justice STEWART took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
